parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion of Front Suspension Cross Member and Control Arm Bracket
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the front suspension cross member and control arm bracket can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle pulls to one side while driving
the steering wheel shakes or vibrates
the vehicle makes a clunking or popping sound
and the front suspension cross member or control arm bracket is rusted or broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Front Brake Rotors and Calipers
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front brake rotors and calipers can cause the vehicle to lose braking power, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates while braking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
and the front brake rotors and calipers are worn out or damaged.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the subframe crossmember can cause the vehicle to vibrate violently, lose control, and potentially lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle shakes or vibrates violently when applying the brakes
the front of the vehicle pulls to one side
the tire rubs against the inner fender
the vehicle becomes difficult to control
and the crossmember collapses or breaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Ignition Key Sticking in Ignition Switch
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The ignition key sticking in the ignition switch can cause inconvenience, delay, and potential safety risks, as the vehicle may be left unlocked and accessible to unauthorized individuals.
symptoms: The key gets stuck in the ignition
the key cannot be removed from the ignition
the key can only be removed by jiggling or wiggling
the key is stuck in the ignition after the vehicle is turned off
the key will not turn to the lock position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlights and interior lights can reduce visibility, increasing the risk of accidents, especially at night or in low-light conditions.
symptoms: The headlights and interior lights flicker
the lights do not function properly
the lights are dim or do not turn on.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause various problems, including engine stalling, loss of power, and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Fuses blow
circuit breakers trip
wires burn or melt
electrical components malfunction.
